      • getFromDeepIdentifier

        public JsonValue getFromDeepIdentifier(java.lang.String ident)
                                throws JsonObject.JsonTraversalException

        Retrieves the JsonValue from JsonObjects nested within this instance, with the given dot-separated string identifier.

        For Example, using the identifier "foo.bar" on a JsonObject representing this structure

        { "baz": 13, "foo": { "bar": "Hello" } }

        would return "Hello" wrapped in a JsonString object

        Parameters:
        ident - The identifier containing one or more levels of object keys, separated with a single dot to denote nested levels of identifiers. e.g. "foo.bar" would retrieve the key "bar" from the "foo" object nested under the root of the JsonObject
        Returns:
        The JsonValue stored under the specified deep identifier, or JsonValue.Null if the key does not exist (but has successfully traversed to the end of the identifier chain)
        Throws:
        JsonObject.JsonTraversalException - If the specified identifier attempts to navigate a level deeper into a value that is not a JsonObject (the identifier specifies a key that cannot be reached).

      • traverseForDeepValue

        public static JsonValue traverseForDeepValue(JsonObject obj,
                                             java.lang.String ident)
                                      throws JsonObject.JsonTraversalException

        Retrieves the JsonValue from JsonObjects nested within a given JsonObject instance, with the given dot-separated string identifier.

        For Example, using the identifier "foo.bar" on a JsonObject representing this structure

        { "baz": 13, "foo": { "bar": "Hello" } }

        would return "Hello" wrapped in a JsonString object

        Parameters:
        obj - The instance of JsonObject to traverse deeper into
        ident - The identifier containing one or more levels of object keys, separated with a single dot to denote nested levels of identifiers. e.g. "foo.bar" would retrieve the key "bar" from the "foo" object nested under the root of the JsonObject
        Returns:
        The JsonValue stored under the specified deep identifier, or JsonValue.Null if the key does not exist (but has successfully traversed to the end of the identifier chain)
        Throws:
        JsonObject.JsonTraversalException - Thrown if the specified identifier attempts to navigate a level deeper into a value that is not a JsonObject (the identifier specifies a key that cannot be reached).

      • traverseForDeepValue

        public static JsonValue traverseForDeepValue(JsonObject obj,
                                             java.lang.String[] identParts)
                                      throws JsonObject.JsonTraversalException

        Retrieves the JsonValue from JsonObjects nested within a given JsonObject instance, with the given array being used in place of a dot seperated identifier.

        For Example, using the identifier "foo.bar" (equivelant "['foo', 'bar']") on a JsonObject representing this structure

        { "baz": 13, "foo": { "bar": "Hello" } }

        would return "Hello" wrapped in a JsonString object

        Parameters:
        obj - The instance of JsonObject to traverse deeper into
        identParts - An array of String keys that will be used to traverse the provided JsonObject. The identifier at index 0 will be the key retrieved from the given JsonObject, and subsequent elements will be used as keys for nested JsonObject instances. If identParts only contains one element, the JsonValue stored under that element will be returned. e.g. "['foo', 'bar']" would retrieve the key "bar" from the "foo" object nested under the root of the JsonObject
        Returns:
        The JsonValue stored under the specified deep identifier, or JsonValue.Null if the key does not exist (but has successfully traversed to the end of the identifier chain)
        Throws:
        JsonObject.JsonTraversalException - Thrown if the specified identifier attempts to navigate a level deeper into a value that is not a JsonObject (the identifier specifies a key that cannot be reached).
